Isithwalandwe Andrew Mlangeni Virtual Memorial Service. JOHANNESBURG - The ANC held a virtual memorial service to honor and celebrate the life of the last remaining Rivonia Trialist Andrew Mlangeni on Sunday. Mlangeni died aged 95 on Tuesday at 1 Military Hospital in Pretoria following an abdominal complaint. READ: Tributes pour in for struggle icon Andrew Mlangeni Mlangeni spent over two decades on Robben Island after he was convicted at the Rivonia Treason trial in 1964. The national flag was flown at half-mast from the morning of Friday, 24 July until the evening of Wednesday, 29 July, the day on which Mlangeni will be laid to rest. Friends, family and colleagues have been paying their respects to the family at their Soweto home.